<br>
I've gotten a joined ethreal cape from one of the named wurms, +4 int +25 mana all/all - tradable, and I've also gotten a runed writ +8 int +3 to all resists +8 wis.  for all int casters and all priests, goes in secondary slot and no drop.  We also got a nice mantle there +agi +str and dex I believe, gave it to a monk.  Also monster summoning 2 dropped from a wurm, and tons of clerics and druid spells as well as bard songs.  Not a bad zone I must say <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And with the new added resists skyshrine is awesome.  <br>
<br>
Breakin is a little tough, there's 5 - 6 guardians in one room, can't be harmonied, can't be mezzed very well because of high MR (might have been changed with the recent patch) and when you pull, 3 of 'em at least will come at you.  We did this break with 53 warrior, 51 druid, 51 mage (me at the time) 51 cleric 48 monk and 49 enchanter.  Once you get past that room, it's pretty easy.  Enchanter's not really needed because you will single pull everything with a druid to harmony.  Enchanter is good for rune and clarity and such.  We took down both the named wurms, the large velium statue (hits HARD! - doubles for around 200) and the wyverns.  It takes a long time to kill them (all very high MR and FR so mostly dependent on melee power) even wizzies have problems landing lures on these guys.  Druid dot sticks very easily, so do necros.  mage spells are basically useless.  I was pumping out mod rods and doing DS most of the time. I managed to get malise off on 3 mobs, and malosi off on 1 mob out of the 50+ that we've killed.   <br>
But with the new patch, mobs in SS have decreased magic resist and I think my guild is going back in either today or tomorrow just to see how everything is now.  Hopefully casters will be a little bit more useful in this zone.  At least us mages have our pets for the melee damage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The book isn't too rare of a drop - I've seen it twice so far, and I've been deep in SS only twice so it's a good chance you'll get one if you go in there.<br>
<br>
